cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning to histopathology image analysis, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained deep convolutional networks and multiple instance learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the challenge of generating ground-truth localized annotations, which is a problem in information retrieval and natural language processing, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of weakly supervised learning, which is a topic in computational linguistics and natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category as well.
